The paper deals with the parameterized complexity and inapproximability of two problems: $k$-ExactCover and $k$-Nearest-Codeword. This suggests that the paper could belong to categories related to computational complexity (cs.CC), data structures and algorithms (cs.DS), information theory (cs.IT), computational geometry (cs.CG), and discrete mathematics (cs.DM). Additionally, the use of the Exponential Time Hypothesis (ETH) and Strong Exponential Time Hypothesis (SETH) in the paper further supports the likelihood of it belonging to cs.CC and cs.DM.
